  "label": "Ashglass Sleep Bay",
  "description": "Ashglass Sleep Bay is a narrow, enclosed bedroom carved into the suite’s blast-thick ferrocrete shell, its ceiling low and its corners squared for structural economy. A mortared-in bunk and recessed storage niches dominate the long wall, their edges capped in chipped enamel to resist wear under constant occupancy. Recessed lumen strips sit behind armored glass slats, casting a controlled, shadow-minimizing light consistent with enclave blackout discipline. Vent grilles and a sealed bulkhead panel mark the room’s integration into Pale Meridian’s rationed air and heat systems.",
